            <h2 id="chapter-title">The Django Book</h2>

<p>Welcome to the online version of The Django Book, a <a href="/license/">free book</a> about the <a href="http://www.djangoproject.com/">Django Web framework</a> for the Python programming language.</p>

<p>The book is available in three versions:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1590597257?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=jacobianorg-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=1590597257">First edition: Apress print book</a></strong>. Covers Django 0.96 (<em>not</em> Django 1.0!).</li>
<li><strong><a href="/en/1.0/">First edition: Free Web version</a></strong>. Identical to print edition. Covers Django 0.96 (<em>not</em> Django 1.0!).</li>
<li><strong>NEW:</strong> <strong><a href="/en/2.0/">Second edition: Web preview</a></strong>. Covers <strong>Django 1.0</strong>. A work in progress, to which you can contribute.</li>
</ul>

<p>Each Web edition of the book lets you add and read comments on a per-paragraph basis, along the left margins. (<a href="/about/comments/">Get help here.</a>) To submit feedback that doesn't fit into the comment system, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.</p>

